import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    # Group by origin and destination airports and sum the counts
    airport_counts = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).sum().reset_index()
    
    # Calculate the total number of flights for each airport
    total_flights = airport_counts.groupby('origin')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    
    # Sort the airports by total number of flights and select the top 10
    top_10_airports = total_flights.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    
    # Create the bar chart
    sns.barplot(x='origin', y='count', data=top_10_airports)
    
    # Rotate x-axis labels if necessary
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What are the top 10 busiest airports in terms of number of flights?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', bins=20)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of number of flights between different airports?", wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    median_count = data['count'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_count, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_count:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import networkx as nx

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    G = nx.from_pandas_edgelist(data, source='origin', target='destination', edge_attr='count', create_using=nx.DiGraph())
    pos = nx.spring_layout(G, seed=42)
    nx.draw(G, pos, node_size=50, node_color='blue', with_labels=True, font_size=8)
    edge_labels = nx.get_edge_attributes(G, 'count')
    nx.draw_networkx_edge_labels(G, pos, edge_labels=edge_labels, font_size=8)
    
    plt.title("What are the most popular routes in terms of number of flights?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
